  "prompt": "What is the required level of education for archaeologists?",
  "response": "To become an archaeologist, a minimum of a bachelor's degree in archaeology, anthropology, or a related field is typically required. Many positions, especially those in research, teaching, or leadership roles, may require a master's degree or even a Ph.D. in archaeology or a closely related discipline. \n\nIn addition to formal education, practical experience gained through fieldwork, internships, or volunteer opportunities is highly valuable in the field of archaeology. Many archaeologists also develop specialized skills or knowledge, such as proficiency in geographic information systems (GIS), dating methods, or specific types of analysis, which can enhance their qualifications.",
